analysed_sst/.zattrs.comment: Interim near-real-time (nrt) version using Multi-Resolution Variational Analysis (MRVA) method for interpolation; to be replaced by Final version
analysed_sst/.zattrs.source: MODIS_T-JPL, MODIS_A-JPL, AMSR2-REMSS, AVHRRMTA_G-NAVO, AVHRRMTB_G-NAVO, iQUAM-NOAA/NESDIS, Ice_Conc-OSISAF

analysis_error/.zattrs.long_name: estimated error standard deviation of analysed_sst

dt_1km_data/.zattrs.comment: The grid value is hours between the analysis time and the most recent MODIS or VIIRS 1km L2P datum within 0.01 degrees from the grid point.  \"Fill value\" indicates absence of such 1km data at the grid point.
dt_1km_data/.zattrs.source: MODIS and VIIRS pixels ingested by MUR

lat/.zattrs.comment: geolocations inherited from the input data without correction

lon/.zattrs.comment: geolocations inherited from the input data without correction

mask/.zattrs.comment: mask can be used to further filter the data.
mask/.zattrs.source: GMT \"grdlandmask\", ice flag from sea_ice_fraction data

sea_ice_fraction/.zattrs.comment: ice fraction is a dimensionless quantity between 0 and 1; it has been interpolated by a nearest neighbor approach.

sst_anomaly/.zattrs.comment: anomaly reference to the day-of-year average between 2003 and 2014
sst_anomaly/.zattrs.long_name: SST anomaly from a seasonal SST climatology based on the MUR data over 2003-2014 period
